.opencode/commands/speckit/README.txt:47:SEARCH ROUTING: semantic or concept code discovery routes to `code_graph_query + Grep`; structural questions about callers, imports, dependencies, outlines, symbols, or impact route to `code_graph_query`; exact literal text or regex checks stay on grep-style search. `session_bootstrap`, `session_resume`, and `/speckit:resume` reuse this same contract.
.opencode/commands/speckit/README.txt:62:| **resume** | `/speckit:resume [spec-folder] [:auto\|:confirm]` | varies | Resume or recover work on an existing spec folder |
.opencode/commands/speckit/README.txt:90:├── resume.md         # /speckit:resume - Resume existing work
.opencode/commands/speckit/README.txt:137:/speckit:resume (continue in a new or interrupted session)
.opencode/commands/speckit/README.txt:200:/speckit:resume specs/012-rate-limiting :auto
.opencode/commands/speckit/README.txt:205:# Optimize skill advisor scoring (now under /doctor:* group, not speckit)
.opencode/commands/speckit/README.txt:226:Yes. `/speckit:resume` loads the best available continuation context for the spec folder even if you never wrote a handover entry. The canonical recovery ladder is `handover.md` -> `_memory.continuity` -> canonical spec docs. If one rung is missing, resume continues with the next packet-local source. If no saved state exists anywhere in that ladder, the command prompts you to start fresh with `/speckit:plan`. Running `/memory:save` before ending a session still improves the first recovery pass, but it is not required.
.opencode/commands/speckit/README.txt:245:| Continuity save adds little context | No significant work in session | Use `/memory:save` after meaningful progress or rely on `/speckit:resume` ladder |
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.4.0.0.md:5:Alongside the memory rewrite, the search stack got smarter, the code graph got safer to traverse, deep-loop skills became fully auditable, and every CLI skill now runs a quality check on its prompts before talking to external models. A cleanup pass on the skill advisor removed dead routing code and added coverage for the kinds of phrases people actually type. The intake command surface also consolidated: `/spec_kit:start` is gone, replaced by `/spec_kit:plan --intake-only` backed by a shared intake contract. 
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.4.0.0.md:40:Session resume checks one clear order: `handover.md` first, then the `_memory.continuity` block inside `implementation-summary.md`, then the spec docs themselves. First source with useful content wins.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.4.0.0.md:44:Session stop hooks autosave by default. Shutting a session no longer loses context.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual-testing-playbook/tooling-and-scripts/json-mode-hybrid-enrichment.md:3:description: "This scenario validates the structured JSON summary contract for generate-context.js, including toolCalls/exchanges fields, file-backed JSON authority, and Wave 2 hardening."
