.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.4.1.0.md:3:v3.4.0.0 shipped the substrate. v3.4.1.0 is the release where you can see it working. The code graph found the bug that was costing it most of its symbols. The skill advisor finally ships as a real daemon backing live hooks across every runtime that has them. The CocoIndex daemon stops leaking processes and log spam under load. And the doctor commands, trust badges, freshness indicators, and telemetry surfaces this release adds are all built so a single command can answer "is this thing healthy right now?"
