.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.1.2.0.md:55:#### Manual-fallback save mode for when generate-context.js is unavailable
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.1.2.0.md:57:During the ESM migration, `generate-context.js` broke because the scripts-to-mcp_server runtime chain crashed on CJS globals in ESM output. Manual memory saves via MCP were blocked by the sufficiency validator (primary evidence = 0). Zero fallback existed. Added manual-fallback source classification in `memory-save.ts` that allows write with deferred indexing when support evidence >= 3 and anchors >= 1. Expanded `markdown-evidence-builder.ts` to parse primary evidence from `Key Decisions`, `Next Steps`, `Outcomes`, and `Implementation State` sections.
.opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep-review.contract.md:311:   - memory_context({ input: review_target OR "deep-review", mode: "focused", includeContent: true })
