.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.2.0.0.md:41:#### Stop-hook tracking and best-effort auto-save
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.2.0.0.md:43:The system had little durable insight into session usage and no reliable way to capture end-of-session state automatically. Stop-hook tracking parses transcript usage data, stores hook-state metrics, estimates token spend, and can trigger a best-effort `generate-context.js` save path when configured thresholds are met.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.2.0.0.md:48:Claude hooks covered only one runtime family. Other runtimes still depended on the AI remembering to prime itself manually. MCP first-call priming, `session_resume`, `session_health`, and `session_bootstrap` were added so hookless runtimes can recover with a single main path. Structural bootstrap expected behaviors and startup briefs were added for OpenCode-style flows.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.2.0.0.md:199:Runtime instructions, context-prime agents, and bootstrap surfaces drifted apart. The same recovery concept had different wording and different guarantees depending on where the AI looked. Non-hook recovery was standardized around explicit expected behaviors: ready/stale/missing structural state, a main `session_bootstrap` path, and mirrored routing/recovery tables across all runtime-facing docs and agent definitions.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.2.0.0.md:298:| `mcp-server/handlers/session-bootstrap.ts` | Canonical hookless bootstrap surface |
