.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature-catalog/context-preservation/passive-context-enrichment.md:21:The spec-doc record-surface and response-hints hooks form a passive enrichment pipeline. On every tool call, constitutional memories and trigger-matched spec-doc records are surfaced and appended to the response envelope. Code graph status is included when available. Token estimation prevents oversized payloads. The enrichment is additive (appended to hints) and does not modify the primary tool response. This ensures AI runtimes always have access to critical context even when they do not explicitly call memory_context.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/handlers/save/README.md:137:| `response-builder.ts` | Converts save results and planner payloads into MCP success or error envelopes, including `metadataRefresh: { refreshed:false, refreshedBy:'generate-context save lane' }` on mutating packet-doc saves where the MCP content-indexing lane did not refresh packet metadata. |
