.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature-catalog/tooling-and-scripts/debug-delegation-scaffold-generator.md:33:The output file always carries five numbered H2 headings: `PROBLEM SUMMARY`, `ATTEMPTED FIXES`, `CONTEXT FOR SPECIALIST`, `RECOMMENDED NEXT STEPS`, and `HANDOFF CHECKLIST`. Each attempt row in `--errors-json` produces a corresponding approach/result entry under ATTEMPTED FIXES. The frontmatter includes a `_memory.continuity` block with `packet_pointer` set to the spec folder relative path and `last_updated_by: "scaffold-debug-delegation.sh"` so continuity reads can locate the handoff.
