.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/cli/memory-handback.md:3:description: Canonical 7-step Memory Handback procedure shared across the three cli-* sibling skills. Covers MEMORY_HANDBACK extraction, structured-JSON normalization, generate-context.js dispatch modes, and the post-010 save gates.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/cli/memory-handback.md:22:Canonical 7-step Memory Handback procedure shared across the three cli-* sibling skills. Covers MEMORY_HANDBACK extraction, structured-JSON normalization, generate-context.js dispatch modes, and the post-010 save gates.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/cli/memory-handback.md:30:3. **Convert to structured JSON**: Build the JSON-primary payload that `generate-context.js` documents. Use `specFolder`, `user_prompts`, `observations`, and `recent_context` as the canonical field names in new examples. Add `FILES`, `sessionSummary`, `keyDecisions`, `nextSteps`, `triggerPhrases`, `toolCalls`, `exchanges`, `preflight`, and `postflight` when the delegated run produced that evidence.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/cli/memory-handback.md:33:6. **Invoke generate-context.js**: Use one of:
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/cli/memory-handback.md:34:   - `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json [spec-folder]`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/cli/memory-handback.md:35:   - `printf '%s' "$JSON_PAYLOAD" | node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js --stdin [spec-folder]`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/cli/memory-handback.md:36:   - `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js --json "$JSON_PAYLOAD" [spec-folder]`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/cli/memory-handback.md:45:**Structured JSON only**: Direct spec-folder-only invocation is no longer supported. Always call `generate-context.js` with `--stdin`, `--json`, or a JSON temp file.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/cli/memory-handback.md:47:**MCP session scoping**: A dispatched cli sub-session should omit `sessionId` on its first Spec Kit Memory call. The trusted-session rejection (`E_SESSION_SCOPE`) is enforced by `memory_context`, `memory_search`, and `memory_match_triggers`; do not assume every sessionId-accepting tool applies the same guard. Omit `sessionId` so the server generates one, then reuse the `effectiveSessionId` returned for calls that stay inside that dispatched session.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/cli/memory-handback.md:51:**Explicit JSON mode failures**: If the explicit data file cannot be loaded, `generate-context.js` fails with `EXPLICIT_DATA_FILE_LOAD_FAILED: ...`. Do not fall back to OpenCode capture in that case; surface the error and stop.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/structure/sub-folder-versioning.md:24:Enable clean separation of iterative work within a single spec folder while preserving historical context through packet continuity. Each iteration maintains its own canonical continuity (the `_memory.continuity` block in its `implementation-summary.md`) plus a git-ignored `scratch/` workspace tied to that child packet.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/structure/sub-folder-versioning.md:46:│   ├── implementation-summary.md   # _memory.continuity block (canonical context)
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/structure/sub-folder-versioning.md:109:- `generate-context.js` refreshes canonical continuity in the specified sub-folder's `implementation-summary.md` `_memory.continuity` block (legacy `[spec]/memory/*.md` writes are retired)
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/structure/sub-folder-versioning.md:158:   - Continuity saves update the sub-folder's `implementation-summary.md` `_memory.continuity` block
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/structure/sub-folder-versioning.md:190:Both systems use the same `###-name/` naming convention for child folders and both keep independent canonical continuity (`implementation-summary.md` `_memory.continuity`) per child.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/structure/sub-folder-versioning.md:196:When using subfolder versioning, the spec-doc record save script (`generate-context.js`) fully supports nested paths.
