.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/memory/save-workflow.md:255:The Phase 018 save path is packet-first. Retired `[spec]/memory/*.md` writes are no longer part of the workflow. `generate-context.js` updates continuity inside the selected packet and reindexes the affected docs.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/memory/save-workflow.md:259:Before canonical continuity files are mutated, `generate-context.js` acquires a packet-local `.canonical-save.lock`. Parallel saves against the same folder fail fast while stale locks are removed with a warning, which keeps simultaneous handoff writes from interleaving.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/memory/save-workflow.md:263:| `implementation-summary.md` | Primary continuity document carrying `_memory.continuity` in frontmatter |
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/memory/save-workflow.md:286:├── implementation-summary.md    # carries _memory.continuity
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/memory/save-workflow.md:295:- **At a phase parent**: skip the `implementation-summary.md` continuity write at parent (parents do not require that file at all). Instead, atomically update the parent's `graph-metadata.json` `derived.last_active_child_id = null` and `derived.last_active_at = ISO_8601_NOW`. Logic at `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/memory/generate-context.ts:493` (`updatePhaseParentPointersAfterSave`).
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/memory/save-workflow.md:296:- **At a child of a phase parent**: write the child's normal `_memory.continuity` to its `implementation-summary.md` AND atomically update the parent's `graph-metadata.json` `derived.last_active_child_id` to the child's `packet_id` plus a fresh `last_active_at`. The bubble-up uses the same atomic write helper.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/memory/save-workflow.md:297:- **Atomic write**: same-directory temp file + `fs.renameSync` (POSIX-atomic). Helper at `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/memory/generate-context.ts:387` (`atomicWriteJson`). Prevents torn JSON state under concurrent saves.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/memory/save-workflow.md:298:- **Resume integration**: `/speckit:resume` reads `derived.last_active_child_id` first when the target is a phase parent. If non-null and `last_active_at` is within 24 hours, recurse directly into that child. Otherwise fall back to listing children with statuses. `--no-redirect` bypasses the pointer entirely.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/memory/save-workflow.md:321:- `implementation-summary.md` carries the thin `_memory.continuity` block.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/memory/save-workflow.md:323:- recovery begins with `handover.md`, then `_memory.continuity`, then the rest of the packet docs.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/memory/save-workflow.md:337:| `metadata_only` | `_memory.continuity` | Machine-owned continuity payloads |
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/memory/save-workflow.md:372:For retrieval, `memory_context()` routes queries across 7 intents (including `find_spec` and `find_decision`) and applies intent-aware weighting.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/memory/save-workflow.md:448:**CRITICAL:** Before implementing ANY changes in a spec folder, rebuild context from canonical packet continuity first: `handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs`.
