.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/continuity/README.md:7:  - "_memory.continuity"
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/continuity/README.md:12:> Thin `_memory.continuity` parsing, validation, serialization, and markdown frontmatter update helpers.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/continuity/README.md:18:`lib/continuity/` owns the thin `_memory.continuity` record contract used in spec-folder markdown frontmatter. It parses frontmatter, validates compact recovery fields, normalizes the record, enforces the byte budget, and writes the record back into markdown without taking over resume orchestration.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/continuity/README.md:23:- The record keeps packet recovery compact with `packet_pointer`, timestamps, action fields, blockers, key files, optional `session_dedup`, completion percentage, and question IDs.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/continuity/README.md:24:- The byte budget is `THIN_CONTINUITY_MAX_BYTES`, currently `2048` bytes for the serialized `_memory.continuity` envelope.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/continuity/README.md:25:- The canonical recovery ladder remains `handover.md` → `_memory.continuity` → spec docs. This folder owns the middle record format only.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/continuity/README.md:38:│ spec folder docs   │      │ _memory.continuity      │
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/continuity/README.md:50:│ body content       │      │ _memory.continuity YAML │
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/continuity/README.md:54:handover.md → _memory.continuity → spec docs
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/continuity/README.md:100:| `thin-continuity-record.ts` | Defines `ThinContinuityRecord`, validates compact fields, serializes the `_memory.continuity` envelope, reads records from markdown or objects, and upserts records into markdown frontmatter. |
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/continuity/README.md:108:| Record ownership | Owns the shape and validation of `_memory.continuity`. |
